FT  19 AUG 92 / UK Company News: City Centre advances to Pounds 4.32m
ALTHOUGH turnover improved 11 per cent and operating profit advanced 26 per
cent in the first half of 1992, directors of City Centre Restaurants
stressed that the comparable period was affected by non-recurring items.
However, operating outcome was some 5 per cent below that made in the first
half of 1990.
Sales were Pounds 42.1m (Pounds 37.9m) and operating profit Pounds 4.06m
(Pounds 3.22m). After interest receivable Pounds 257,00 (Pounds 33,000) and
property disposals Pounds 4,000 (debit Pounds 34,000), the pre-tax profit
was Pounds 4.32m (Pounds 3.22m).
Earnings per share were 1.57p (1.17p) and the interim dividend is held at
0.45p.
